Former soldier Jason takes command of his military wedding to his bride-to-be Sacha. Having served in the army for seven years, Jason wants to celebrate the heroes of WWII by getting Sacha to travel to her wedding in an old war plane, then a tank. But Sacha is hoping the army days are long behind her and is desperate for a traditional, intimate wedding.
With a mother-in-law to impress and a bride hoping he will put her first, will Jason convince Sacha to sign up for his plans, or will he have to run for cover?
